{"id":2696,"date":"2012-03-31T08:52:53","date_gmt":"2012-03-31T04:52:53","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=2696"},"modified":"2024-10-17T06:44:14","modified_gmt":"2024-10-17T02:44:14","slug":"quran-sunnah-then-ijtihad","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/03\/31\/quran-sunnah-then-ijtihad\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Ijtihad: Judge with the Quran, Sunnah, then your opinion"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Al-Harith ibn &#8216;Amr reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, sent Mu\u2019adh to Yemen and he said, \u201c<strong>How will you judge?<\/strong>\u201d Mu\u2019adh said, \u201cI will judge according to the Book of Allah.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>What if it is not in the Book of Allah?<\/strong>\u201d Mu\u2019adh said, \u201cThen, with the Sunnah of the messenger of Allah.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>What if it is not in the Sunnah of the Messenger of Allah?<\/strong>\u201d Mu\u2019adh said, \u201cThen, I will strive to form an opinion.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>All praise is due to Allah, who has made suitable the messenger of the Messenger of Allah.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 1327<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><i>Sahih\u00a0<\/i><\/strong>(authentic) according to Ibn Abdul Barr<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u062d\u064e\u0627\u0631\u0650\u062b\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0645\u0652\u0631\u064d \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0651 \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0628\u064e\u0639\u064e\u062b\u064e \u0645\u064f\u0639\u064e\u0627\u0630\u064b\u0627 \u0625\u0650\u0644\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u064a\u064e\u064